KW  - Universal banking
KW  - Risk-taking
KW  - Commerce
KW  - Investment efficiency
KW  - Social welfare
AB  - This paper analyzes the welfare implications of banks taking equity stakes in firms under conditions of imperfect information and moral hazard. Two cases of bank control over investment decisions are analyzed. In the first, the bank does not control the investment decisions of the firm. Here, the investment efficiency is higher and bank risk is lower for an optimal positive level of bank equity holdings. However, in the case when the bank has veto power over investment proposals by the firm, there is a trade off between increased investment efficiency and increased bank risk.
