KW  - Separation
KW  - Stock returns
AB  - This undertakes a comparative analysis of the stock market perception of the risk of large BHCs and nonfinancial sectors over the 1969–1989 period. This is done by examining industry portfolio returns and their interest rate and default risk sensitivities in relation to economic and industry risk factors. The findings provide no strong basis for concluding that a less risky banking system would result from the removal of the barrier separating banking and commerce.
